approve(address,uint256).details: See {IERC20-approve}. NOTE: If `value` is the maximum `uint256`, the allowance is not updated on `transferFrom`. This is semantically equivalent to an infinite approval. Requirements: - `spender` cannot be the zero address.

buyProperty(uint8,address).details: enables players to purchase properties from the bank

params.buyer: Address of the player that is making the purchase
params.propertyId: The id of the property on the monopoly board

constructor.details: Initializes the contract with a fixed supply of tokens._mint an internal function that mints the total token needed for the game.

decimals().details: Returns the number of decimals used to get its user representation. For example, if `decimals` equals `2`, a balance of `505` tokens should be displayed to a user as `5.05` (`505 / 10 ** 2`). Tokens usually opt for a value of 18, imitating the relationship between Ether and Wei. This is the default value returned by this function, unless it's overridden. NOTE: This information is only used for _display_ purposes: it in no way affects any of the arithmetic of the contract, including {IERC20-balanceOf} and {IERC20-transfer}.

makeDecisionOnProposal(address,uint256,b.details: function that users use to either accept or reject proposal

params._user: address of the user that wants to either accept or reject trade
params.isAccepted: a boolean that users pass to either accept or reject proposal
params.proposalId: Id of the users proposal to be acted upon

makeProposal(address,address,uint8,uint8.details: allows players to propose a trade with other players

params.amountInvolved: the amount of the trade to be carried out
params.biddingPropertyId: optional id of the users property he wants to put in  the transcation
params.otherPlayer: Address of the player the user want to propose a trade with
params.proposedPropertyId: optional id of the property the user wants to buy

transferFrom(address,address,uint256).details: See {IERC20-transferFrom}. Skips emitting an {Approval} event indicating an allowance update. This is not required by the ERC. See {xref-ERC20-_approve-address-address-uint256-bool-}[_approve]. NOTE: Does not update the allowance if the current allowance is the maximum `uint256`.
